Former Senator, Shehu Sani has unveiled 12 things to be achieved by his government if he is elected governor of Kaduna State. DAILY POST recalls that the former lawmaker on Sunday declared his interest to run for governor of the state, claiming he would clean up the “mess” of the current government. In a post on his verified Facebook page on Monday titled: “My Talakawa Agenda for Kaduna State, 2023-2027”, the former lawmaker vowed to end banditry and terrorism currently ravaging the state. The post reads, “My Talakawa Agenda for Kaduna State. 2023-2027 “Ending Banditry and terrorism and securing the lives of our people by consistent and technical support for all security agencies located in the state. “Uniting the People of Northern and Southern Kaduna for peace, equity, justice and prosperity. “Verification and payment of the state debt burden. “Re-industrialisation of the state; reactivation of moribund industries and massive support for small and medium enterprises. “Infrastructural development of neglected rural areas. “Cancellation of open and hidden fees and sundry charges in public schools and public hospitals. “Massive and mechanised agricultural scheme and agro-allied industries to maximumly explore the agro potentials of the state. “Establishment of two new universities for Medicine, Engineering and ICT. “Rescuing the Sports sector and relaunching Kaduna to the top of the sports table in the country. “Cooperation and support for religious groups and traditional institutions for security, peace and development. “Massive building of housing projects and the establishment of Satelite towns in Zaria, Kafanchan and Kaduna. “Other more important things I’ll do I keep to myself for now”.